						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up on the northern side of the central shrine of the Talakaṇṭamma temple.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇarāya, 1518 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1440, Bahudhānya, Vaiśākha śu. 5,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1518 A.D., April 15, (Thursday.)</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a <hi rend="italic">dasavanda</hi> gift of land by the <hi rend="italic">sthānaṁvāru</hi> of Dēviguḍi to Basavana, Matsanāgana and Mudukana, sons of Nāgajiyya of Dēviguḍi, for the merit of king Kṛishṇarāya and Sāḷuva Gōvindarāju Voḍayalu.</p>						

						</summary>
